в”Ӯ The crash was caused by a faulty assumption in an `instcombine` optimization pattern for   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `icmp` on `or`'d `select` instructions. The pattern failed to account for cases involving  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ a scalar `select` condition with vector results, leading to an attempt to create a binary  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ operation with mismatched operand types. The proposed fix corrects this by splatting the   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ scalar condition into a vector, ensuring type consistency and preventing the crash. This   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ allows the optimization to apply correctly to a wider range of vector code patterns.       в”Ӯ
