в”Ӯ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The LLVM `opt` tool crashes with a SIGABRT signal due to an assertion failure in           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `llvm::BinaryOperator::Create`. The assertion `S1->getType() == S2->getType()` fails,      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ indicating an attempt to create a binary instruction (like `and` or `or`) with two         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ operands of different types. This happens within the `instcombine` pass when processing    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the provided LLVM IR.                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The backtrace clearly points to the function `foldICmpBinOpEqualityWithConstant` in        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `InstCombineCompares.cpp` as the source of the problem. The sequence of calls is:          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `visitICmpInst` -> `foldICmpInstWithConstant` -> `foldICmpBinOpWithConstant` ->            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `foldICmpBinOpEqualityWithConstant`                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ This flow indicates that `instcombine` is trying to simplify an `icmp` instruction whose   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ left-hand side is a binary operator and whose right-hand side is a constant. The `opt`     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ debug log confirms that the instruction being visited is `%cmp = icmp ne <4 x i32> %or,    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ zeroinitializer`. The crash occurs when `instcombine` tries to create a new instruction to в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ replace this `icmp`.                                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The specific optimization pattern at fault is designed to transform expressions of the     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ form `icmp eq/ne (or (select cond, C1, C2), X), 0`. In our reproducer:                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `%cmp` is `icmp ne <4 x i32> %or, zeroinitializer`.                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `%or` is `or <4 x i32> %sel, %x`.                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `%sel` is `select i1 %cond, <4 x i32> splat (i32 1), <4 x i32> zeroinitializer`.       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ This matches the pattern where:                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `Cmp` is `%cmp` (an `icmp ne` with a zero constant).                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `BO` is `%or`.                                                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   The left operand of `%or` is a `select` instruction (`%sel`).                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ Inside `foldICmpBinOpEqualityWithConstant`, the code at lines 3628-3636 attempts the       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ following transformation:                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `(icmp ne (or (select cond, NonZero, 0), Other), 0) -> (or cond, (icmp ne Other, 0))`      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ In our case:                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `cond` is the scalar `i1 %cond`.                                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ -   `Other` is the vector `<4 x i32> %x`.                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The transformation logic then constructs:                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1.  A new comparison: `Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(ICMP_NE, Other, ...)` which results в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ in a `<4 x i1>` vector.                                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2.  A new binary operator: `BinaryOperator::Create(Instruction::Or, Cmp, Cond)`.           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ This is where the error occurs. The `BinaryOperator::Create` call attempts to create an    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `or` instruction with operands `Cmp` (type `<4 x i1>`) and `Cond` (type `i1`). LLVM IR     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ does not allow binary logical operations between a vector and a scalar of different types. в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The code incorrectly assumes that if the `select` instruction produces a vector, its       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ condition operand must also be a vector of the same width.                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The fix is to detect this type mismatch and make the types compatible. If the `select`     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ condition is a scalar and the other operands are vectors, the scalar condition must be     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ broadcast (splatted) into a vector of the same width as the other operands before creating в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the final `or` instruction.                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ Two places in the function need this fix, as there are two similar transformation patterns в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ (the "easy case" and the "harder case").                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ To fix this, I will add checks in `foldICmpBinOpEqualityWithConstant` to splat the scalar  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ condition into a vector when necessary.                                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ **Edit Point 1:** For the first transformation case.                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```cpp                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ // File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ // Insert before line 3631:                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         if (auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Other->getType()))                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ           if (!isa<VectorType>(Cond->getType()))                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ             Cond = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(VecTy->getElementCount(), Cond);              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ **Edit Point 2:** For the second transformation case (the "harder case").                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```cpp                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ // File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ // Insert before line 3654:                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         Value *NotCond = Builder.CreateNot(Cond);                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ         if (auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Other->getType()))                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ           if (!isa<VectorType>(NotCond->getType()))                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ             NotCond = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(VecTy->getElementCount(), NotCond);        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ```                                                                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The crash is due to a bug in an `instcombine` optimization that fails to handle a type     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ mismatch between a scalar `select` condition and vector operands. By adding logic to splat в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ the scalar condition into a vector, we ensure type compatibility for the newly created     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ binary instruction, thus fixing the crash and allowing the optimization to work correctly  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ for this vector code pattern.                                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ --------------------  END  --------------------                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
