в”Ӯ The previous patch failed a regression test. The test `icmp-or-of-select-with-zero.ll`     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ specifically checks that the transformation I enabled is *not* performed for the           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ reproducer's code pattern.                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The transformation `(icmp ne (or (select cond, C1, 0), X), 0) -> (or (icmp ne X, 0),       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ cond)` is generally valid, but can be a performance pessimization. The original code has a в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ vector `select`, which might be lowered to a single `blend` instruction on some targets.   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The transformed code introduces a vector `icmp`, a splat of the condition, and a vector    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ `or`. This is often more instructions and may not be faster.                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ The test exists to prevent this pessimization. My previous fix enabled the transformation, в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ causing the test to fail. The correct approach is to disable this specific transformation  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ when it might be a pessimization, which is the case for the reproducer.                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ I will revert the changes I made and instead add a check to prevent the transformation     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ from occurring when the `select` instruction has vector-typed arms but a scalar condition. в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ This will fix the crash without breaking the performance-related regression test.          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ First, I will revert the file to its original state.                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                                                                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ <tool_call>                                                                                в”Ӯ
